cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a meta-optimizer for optimization and machine learning tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning to optimize. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely categories as the proposed meta-optimizer uses LSTMs and population-based optimization algorithms. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the update formula and the use of uncertainty measures. Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper only briefly mentions the protein-docking application, which is related to computer-aided drug design.
